# SDCoreJS SDLC Agent

Use `skills/**/*.md` frontmatter for dispatch. Runtime-localized output is required.

Workflow:

```text
sdcorejs-brainstorming
-> sdcorejs-spec (approval gate + approved spec snapshot)
-> sdcorejs-plan (approval gate + approved plan snapshot)
-> sdcorejs-execute-plan
   always ask sequential vs parallel
-> executor: sdcorejs-angular | sdcorejs-nestjs | sdcorejs-nextjs | sdcorejs-product | sdcorejs-design | sdcorejs-test | generic harness
-> finish gate and tail chain
```

Rules:

- For any non-trivial execution task, use `_refs/shared/tasklist.md`.
- Create the `Tasks` section before work starts and update it as work progresses.
- For long or interruptible work, mirror visible `Tasks` progress to `.sdcorejs/tasks/current-session.md`.
- This applies across explore, git, review, debug, ship, dependency updates, code modification, PR/changelog generation, and verification-before-done.
- Do not say "done", "ready", or "safe to ship" unless verification is complete or skipped verification is explicitly disclosed.
- Requirements before code.
- Apply `_refs/shared/project-context.md` before non-trivial skill execution.
- Explicit approval required for spec and plan.
- Approved plans execute through `sdcorejs-execute-plan`.
- Parallel work requires `sdcorejs-parallel-dispatch`.
- Product/PO docs and traceability use `sdcorejs-product`.
- UI/UX design, wireframes, PNG previews, and FE handoff use `sdcorejs-design`.
- Test-only plans use `sdcorejs-test`.
- Explore codebase context with `sdcorejs-explore`; verify and ship through `sdcorejs-ship`; commit, PR, changelog, and release notes through `sdcorejs-git`.
- Preserve the user's language and locale marks.
- Verify before claiming pass/fixed/done.
